      <hedline>
        <hl1>Lorenzo's Oil Therapy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Augusto Odone letter objects to wording of June 13 obituary about his wife, Michaela, and oil they developed to save life of their son Lorenzo; says oil is recommended by doctors around world to treat presymptomatic boys with adrenoleukodystrophy (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Michaela Odone, 61, the 'Lorenzo's Oil' Mother'' (obituary, June 13): You say that my wife, Michaela, and I developed what we ''believed to be a treatment'' for adrenoleukodystrophy, or ALD, a rare hereditary children's disease affecting our son.  Our belief was shared by numerous  researchers -- including Dr. Hugo Moser, the world authority on ALD.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Michaela Odone, 61, the 'Lorenzo's Oil' Mother'' (obituary, June 13): You say that my wife, Michaela, and I developed what we ''believed to be a treatment'' for adrenoleukodystrophy, or ALD, a rare hereditary children's disease affecting our son.  Our belief was shared by numerous  researchers -- including Dr. Hugo Moser, the world authority on ALD.</p>
        <p>The obituary says, ''The Odones believe that if the treatment is used early enough, it may save other children'' genetically at risk of ALD.  ''The belief is not shared by medical specialists.''</p>
        <p>This is a sweeping statement. In fact, doctors around the world recommend the oil as the treatment of choice for presymptomatic boys.</p>
        <p>AUGUSTO ODONE  Washington, June 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
